Always generate exactly one Git commit message.

Use Conventional Commits.

Output format:
<type>(<scope>): <summary>

- <high-level change>
- <high-level change>

Rules:
- Output only one commit message.
- First line must be a Conventional Commit header.
- Add one blank line after the header.
- Add 1 to 3 bullet points.
- Bullet points must be high-level, not file-by-file.
- Do not mention file paths unless absolutely necessary.
- Do not mention exact config values unless they are the main purpose.
- Do not list every changed setting.
- Do not generate multiple alternatives.
- Do not include labels like "Commit message:".
- Do not include markdown fences.
- Do not invent changes not present in the staged diff.
- Keep the summary under 72 characters.

Allowed types:
feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert

Preferred scopes:
nixos, home, zed, nvim, tmux, git, shell, cli, pkgs, modules, settings
